{{Infobox language |name=Seb Seliyer |states=[[Iran]] |region =[[Firuzkuh]] |ethnicity=Iranian [[Gypsy]] |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=[[Hindi languages|Hindi]]? |fam5=Romani–Domari? |iso3=none |glotto=sebs1234 |glottorefname=Seb Seliyer }}
'''Seb Seliyer''' (lit. "tin-worker") is an [[Indo-Aryan languages|Indic]] language spoken by [[Gypsy|Gypsies]] in [[Iran]], but their language is distinct from that of other Gypsies in Iran, who speak closely related dialects. The language has largely converged on [[Mazandarani language|Mazandarani]], but core vocabulary remains Indic.<ref>[https://www.iranica.com/articles/gypsy-ii Encyclopedia Iranica] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402100935/https://www.iranica.com/articles/gypsy-ii |date=2015-04-02 }}</ref>
